{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The new Link Presentation framework enables app developers to easily present URLs in a rich, beautiful, and consistent way. Learn how to use Link Presentation to retrieve metadata from a URL, present the rich link content inside your app, and provide link metadata to the new share sheet experience in iOS."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-262-Embedding-and-Sharing-Visually-Rich-Links","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc19\/262","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (6 min)","type":"reference"}},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC19","role":"sampleCode","title":"Embedding and Sharing Visually Rich Links","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-262-embedding-and-sharing-visually-rich-links"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Introduction","anchor":"Introduction","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In iOS 10 and macOS Sierra, Messages got Rich Links to make URLs more beautiful and useful. Rich links were customized for certain types of media, including audio\/video playback, Twitter tweets, Apple Maps links, and more.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS 13 and macOS 10.15 introduce new APIs that allow developers to put Rich Links in their own apps.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The video shows how to turn a table view of recipe links into Rich Links. Our starting point looks like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC19-262-starting_point"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Retrieving metadata","anchor":"Retrieving-metadata","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC19-262-lp_metadata_diagram","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LPMetadataProvider"},{"type":"text","text":" class takes a URL and returns an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LPLinkMetadata"},{"type":"text","text":" object with the title and any available media."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s assume we’re configuring a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UITableViewCell"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let metadataProvider = LPMetadataProvider()","let url = URL(string: \"https:\/\/www.apple.com\/ipad\")!","","metadataProvider.startFetchingMetadata(for: url) { metadata, error in","  if error != nil {","    \/\/ The fetch failed; handle the error.","    \/\/ Examples: server doesn't respond, is too slow, user doesn't have network.","    return","  }","","  \/\/ Make use of the fetched metadata.","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":4,"text":"Things to keep in mind with `LPMetadataProvider` and `LPLinkMetadata`.","anchor":"Things-to-keep-in-mind-with-LPMetadataProvider-and-LPLinkMetadata","type":"heading"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Title, icon, image, and video are all optional.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LPLinkMetadata"},{"text":" is serializable with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSSecureCoding"},{"text":". This means you can and should cache metadata locally as much as possible.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Can also be used for local file URLs. Quick Look provides the thumbnail for the file if possible."}]}]}]},{"level":3,"text":"Presenting links","anchor":"Presenting-links","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC19-262-lp_link_view"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Continuing the previous example, replace"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Make use of the fetched metadata"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"with the following","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let linkView = LPLinkView(metadata: metadata)","cell.contentView.addSubview(linkView)","linkView.sizeToFit()"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Our app now looks like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC19-262-rich_links"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that "},{"code":"LPLinkView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has an intrinsic size, but it also responds to "},{"code":"sizeThatFits()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for an ideal size given the surrounding constraints, and it will try to present a layout that’s reasonable at any size."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Accelerating the iOS 13 share sheet","anchor":"Accelerating-the-iOS-13-share-sheet","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For existing apps that share URLs, the share sheet will automatically present a preview of the link at the top of the card.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC19-262-link_at_top","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"However, this requires reaching out to the server to retrieve metadata ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"once the share sheet is presented","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", so the title and icon show up asynchronously.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you already have the metadata, you can send it to the share sheet and the preview will appear instantly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Provide prefetched metadata to UIActivityViewController in your implementation","\/\/ of UIActivityItemSource","","func activityViewControllerLinkMetadata(_: UIActivityViewController) -> LPLinkMetadata? {","  return self.metadata","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Also, when the user chooses to pass that metadata on, say by sending a message, that preview appears instantly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Lastly, you can provide custom or missing metadata information inside the ","type":"text"},{"code":"activityViewControllerLinkMetadata(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["func activityViewControllerLinkMetadata(_: UIActivityViewController) -> LPLinkMetadata? {","  let metadata = LPLinkMetadata()","","  \/\/ `originalURL` and `url` fields are required. Everything else is optional.","  metadata.originalURL = URL(string: \"https:\/\/www.example.com\/apple-pie\")","  metadata.url = metadata.originalURL","  metadata.title = \"The Greatest Apple Pie In The World\"","  metadata.imageProvider = NSItemProvider.init(","    contentsOf: Bundle.main.url(forResource: \"apple-pie\", withExtension: \"jpg\")","  )","  return metadata","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"text":"Summary","anchor":"Summary","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC19-262-summary","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Written By","anchor":"Written-By","type":"heading"},{"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"https:\/\/avatars.githubusercontent.com\/u\/8892223?v=4"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Sarthak Khillon","anchor":"Sarthak-Khillon"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\